[1] Rabid Raccoon in Georgia
Date: 6 Jul 2020
Source: Natural Unseen Hazards [edited]
<http://naturalunseenhazards.wordpress.com/2010/07/09/rabies-reports-from-connecticut-georgia-louisiana-maryland-new-york-north-carolina-2-and-pennsylvania/>


Tony Frank's dogs are being called heroes after they stopped a
suspected rabid raccoon. "We had the dogs out after dinner for their
romp around," said Frank. "At some point, the neighbors' dog chased
the raccoon across the street into our yard and my dogs attacked it."

Frank's dogs Molly and Frank killed the raccoon. Franks then called
Cherokee County Animal Control. It picked up the raccoon and turned
it over to the county's Environmental Health Department which tested
the animal for rabies and discovered it was in fact rabid, the 3rd
such case in North Georgia in the last few weeks. Fortunately, Franks
said he knew what to do.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[This brief article deserves comments now rather than at the end of
the posting. This article does not tell us if the dogs were
vaccinated, or what the authorities did as far as quarantining the
dogs. Unvaccinated dogs with direct contact of a rabid animal are
generally euthanized as they represent a direct hazard to their
owners. We hope Frank's dogs were vaccinated. - Mod.TG]

