[2] Rabid Raccoon in Florida
Date: 9 Jul 2010
Source: The Ledger [edited]
<http://www.theledger.com/article/20100709/NEWS/7095033/1338>


A raccoon captured and killed by Polk County Sheriff's Animal Control
officers Wednesday [7 Jul 2010] tested positive for rabies, the
Sheriff's Office said Friday.

Officers responded to a residence in the Hallamwood Court vicinity,
where a homeowner's dog had attacked the raccoon in the yard.

Residents within a 5-mile radius were advised of the incident. The
homeowner's dog will be quarantined for 180 days. For more
information, call the Animal Control office at 499-2600.

