[5] Maryland tourist attraction has rabid cat
Date: 9 Jul 2010
Source: WBAL TV [edited]
<http://www.wbaltv.com/news/24202578/detail.html>


Health officials in Ocean City said they've confirmed that a cat
found in West Ocean City has tested positive for rabies. The female
cat and a kitten were found in the 11 800 block of Ocean Gateway
(Route 50) near the Ocean City Animal Hospital and the WACS Center on
Tuesday [6 Jul 2010] night.

Authorities said the cat had a white underside with black and orange
markings down the head, back and tail. The kitten, about 8 weeks old,
was solid black except for a small white spot on its neck.

Police said the adult cat was tested Wednesday [7 Jul 2010] because
of its unusual behavior and tested positive on Thursday. The kitten
is still being tested.

Anyone who may have come in contact with either animal should contact
the Worcester County Health Department at 410-632-1100 and select option No. 8.

--
