[7] People in Virginia exposed to rabies
Date: 13 Jul 2010
Source: Hampton Roads.com [edited]
<http://hamptonroads.com/2010/07/health-officials-rabid-animals-found-norfolk-newport-news>


Several people and a dog were exposed to a stray cat that was
reported to officials on 7 Jul 2010, according to the Norfolk
Department of Public Health. The orange, short-haired adult cat was
found in the 3200 block of Vimy Ridge Avenue.

Residents who may have come into contact with 2 rabid animals in
Norfolk and Newport News are being asked to contact health officials.

The cat was known to come into contact with people and other animals
on Vimy Ridge, West Tanners Creek Drive, Bapaume Avenue and Dunkirk
Avenue, a news release says. Health officials have begun treating the
people who have reported being in contact with the cat, the release
says. Without treatment, the disease can be fatal.

Officials are reminding residents to vaccinate their pets against
rabies and to keep them confined to their home or yard. Keep yards
free of food that could attract animals, and avoid contact with wild
animals. Report animal bites or scratches to health officials.

--
