[8] New Jersey raccoon has rabies
Date: 14 Jul 2010
Source: NJ Today [edited]
<http://njtoday.net/2010/07/14/raccoon-found-in-avenel-tests-postive-for-rabies/>


The Woodbridge Township Department of Health & Human Services has
been notified by the New Jersey Department of Health of a positive
case of rabies in a raccoon trapped on 10 Jul 2010 in the vicinity of
the Old Post Inn, located at 750 Route 1 North in Avenel.

Dennis M. Green, Director of Health, and the Woodbridge Township
Department of Health & Human Services urge caution when encountering
suspect animals.

